This page summarises methods for post-occupancy evaluation.
The attached document is a section of this thesis, for more information and references:
https://repository.lboro.ac.uk/articles/Energy_efficiency_refurbishment_of_UK_owner-occupied_homes_the_householders_perspective/9453971

*Pre retrofit data collection
Engagement with householders: expectations, goals, costs etc
Energy meter readings
Building survey
Temperature monitoring (indoor and out)
Relative humidity or air quality monitoring
Test air leakage
Modelling based on Building Research Establishmentâ€™s Domestic Energy Model (BREDEM) methodology

*Post retrofit data collection
Engagement with householders: Experiences, actual changes, costs etc
Energy meter readings
Temperature monitoring (indoor and out)
Relative humidity or air quality monitoring
Test air leakage
Update BREDEM model

